addNewLocation.activateManual.bodyConten: Activate your TellStick by typing the activation code. The activation code is written on the label on the bottom of your TellStick.
addNewLocation.activateManual.invalidAct: The activation code you entered is invalid. Please check that it is entered correctly.
addNewLocation.activateManual.label: Activation Code
addNewLocation.locationName.invalidLocat: Location name can not be empty
addNewLocation.locationName.label: Name
addNewLocation.position.dialogueBodyPara: The geographic position is used for calculating correct sunrise and sunset times for scheduled events
If you want to skip this step you can just click next without entering anything
Press and hold the marker to change the position manually
addNewLocation.position.label: Address
addNewLocation.success.messageBodyParaOn: You have now taken the first step towards your smart home! Now you can start adding devices, view sensors, schedule devices and events and much more.
addNewLocation.success.messageBodyParaTw: If you want help or would like to learn tips and tricks on how to setup your smart home you can view our guides by clicking below
changeLog.WizardFour.description: You can easily dim your dimmable devices directly from the device list by holding and dragging the action button up or down. Drag up to dim up and down to dim to a lower value.
changeLog.WizardFour.title: Dim your device by holding and dragging
changeLog.WizardTwo.description: In this version we have also added the functionality to add your location directly in the app. This is done in a step-by-step wizard for easy setup.
changeLog.WizardTwo.title: Add your location right here in the app
changeLog.wizardFive.description: Enjoy the app in your native language! The language in the app is detected automatically based on the selected language on your device.
changeLog.wizardFive.title: Support for multiple languages
changeLog.wizardOne.description: If you don't have an account already you can now do that in the app without the need of a computer.
changeLog.wizardOne.title: Create account to get started
changeLog.wizardThree.description: Click on a device to see extended information and history for that device. You can see what location it is connected to and when it was controlled and from what platform.
changeLog.wizardThree.title: Updated device details and device history
